Python was invented in late 1980s by Guido van Rossum at Centrum Wiskunde & informatika (CWI) in the Netherlands as a successor to the ABC programing language, which was inspired by SETL, cabable of exeption handing and interfacing with the Amoeba operating system. Its implementasion began in December 1989. Van Rossum shouldered sole responsibly for the project, as the lead developer, until 122 July 2018, when he announced his "permanent vacation" from his responsibilities as Pythons "benevolent dictator for life" *(BDFL), a title the python community bestowed upon him to teflect his long-tern commitment as the project's chief descision-maker (he has sinse come out of retirement and is self-titled "BDFL-emeritus"). in january 2019, active python core developers elected a five-member Steering council to lead the project.
